This paper discusses the extension of the Shannon-Weaver model of linear information transmission to include meaning and organization in networks of inter-human communication. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including computational linguistics (cs.CL), social and information networks (cs.SI), systems and control (cs.SD), cybernetics (cs.CY), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically mentions the use of the vector space model, which is commonly used in computational linguistics and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.SI and cs.SD, and then cs.CY.
